          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The production was accomplished by using the reaction",
                "3He+6Li with the two proton transfer channel",
                "3He(6Li,n) 8B leading to 8B. A primary bunched beam",
                "of 6Li was accelerated at 37 MeV by the UND FN tandem",
                "and impinged on a 2.5-cm-long gas target of 3He at a",
                "pressure of 850 Torr. Secondary beams were produced",
                "at energies of 27.7 MeV for 8B, 20.1 MeV for 7Be, and",
                "14.9 MeV for 7Li."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD",
                "TELES"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The reaction products, including",
                "elastically scattered particles, were detected in",
                "four two-stage dE-E telescopes. Each of these",
                "consisted of a double-sided silicon strip detector",
                " (DSSSD) and a pad silicon detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A natZr target of 1.95 mg/cm2 thickness."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The elastically scattered 8B nuclei were very",
                "well separated from the other beam products with the",
                "dE-E technique."
              ]
            }
          ],
